.TH MYTORRENT "1" "January 2026" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mytorrent \- Torrent client launcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mytorrent
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,TORRENT_FILE\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mytorrent
is a launcher script for torrent clients. It detects available torrent applications and launches the preferred client, supporting both graphical and console-based torrent applications.
.PP
The script provides a unified interface for opening torrent files regardless of which client is installed on the system.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Set the download directory
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B mytorrent
Launch the default torrent client
.TP
.B mytorrent file.torrent
Open a torrent file with the default client
.TP
.B mytorrent --dir ~/Downloads
Launch client with specified download directory
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/mytorrent/settings.conf
User configuration file for mytorrent preferences
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/mytorrent/
Log file directory for error tracking
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MYTORRENT_CLIENT
Override the default torrent client selection
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error
.TP
.B 3
No torrent client found
